Level 2 Screening with PanTum® Detect Blood Test

We invite you to get yourself screened with PanTum® Detect blood test developed to identify symptomless healthy individuals with silent tumor growth within the critical detection point.

PanTum® Detect blood test provides indications of elevated concentrations of universal pan tumor biomarkers i.e. DNaseX(Apo10) and TKTL1 in macrophages (scavenger immune cells) from a single draw of human EDTA whole blood. The PanTum® Detect blood test identifies symptomless healthy individuals with elevated tumor biomarkers in macrophages, indicating a potential risk of tumor growth advancing to dangerous stages of cancer development.

THE BEST REMEDY FOR CANCER IS TO NEVER LET IT ADVANCE IN THE FIRST PLACE

The fight against cancer begins with counselling healthy individuals to fearlessly embrace screening interventions ideally covering multiple cancers simultaneously. Greater exposure to cancer-causing factors enhances the personal benefits of screening with PanTum® Detect blood test, which is developed to identify symptomless individuals with cell damage in benign and localized malignant stages of cancer development.

The introduction of PanTum® Detect screening blood test in India offers asymptomatic healthy residents protection against delayed cancer detection, specially recommended for those with family history of cancer and exposure to cancer causing lifestyle factors, chemicals or toxins.

Regular “screening” of asymptomatic healthy individuals with PanTum® Detect blood test maximizes the chances of timely detection of tumors before they turn dangerous, reducing the risk of cancer progressing unnoticed to life-threatening late stages.

PANTUM® DETECT PREVENTION CONCEPT

Cancer can grow unnoticed in the body for years as a tumor remains locally confined before it develops into an invasive and aggressive form. By the time symptoms are noticeable, the disease has often progressed such that the chances of successful treatment and recovery are significantly reduced. The time of detection is therefore crucial for the success of treatment and survival; the earlier a tumor is detected, the higher the chances of effective treatment and recovery.

We therefore recommend performing a PanTum® Detect screening blood test every year to maximize the chances of detecting a dangerous and aggressive tumor in time. Such localized and early detected tumors can usually be treated successfully.

PanTum® Detect is the ultimate defense against potential delay in cancer detection.

Regular screening with PanTum® Detect blood test will identify individuals with silently growing tumors just before they turn dangerous. Consecutive negative PanTum® Detect results protect the screened individuals from potential delay in cancer detection.

PAN TUMOR EARLY DETECTION PROGRAM

Benefits and Limitations

associated with Pan-Tumor Early Detection Program

A personal decision for the screening candidate
The decision to test with PanTum® Detect is a personal one for every individual. The individual needs to be aware of limitations and should weigh these against the benefits of annual screening with PanTum® Detect.

Benefits Limitations

For asymptomatic healthy individuals getting tested with PanTum® Detect blood test

  • PanTum® Detect is a simple blood test for indications of almost all types of cancer.
  • PanTum® Detect is a simple blood test & has an IVD CE validated high sensitivity of 97.5% (true positives) & specificity of 99% (true negatives).
  • PanTum® Detect is ideal for preventive health checks, offering protection against delayed cancer detection. Regular annual screening with this blood test improves the chance of identifying early-stage tumors, reducing the risk of late diagnosis even before symptoms appear.
  • Only those screened candidates who test positive with PanTum® Detect are exposed to standard protocols for early-stage cancer detection pathology & imaging diagnostics.
  • Early cancer detection with PanTum® Detect reduces avoidable deaths and lowers medical costs compared to late-stage treatment.

For financial sponsors of screening with PanTum® Detect blood test

  • Employees, their dependents, and policyholders who use PanTum® Detect benefit from timely detection, leading to reduced cancer risk coverage costs.
  • Documented evidence of lower cancer risk exposure will lead to reduction in group health insurance premiums.
  • Healthier, protected, and engaged employee base with reduced succession risk for Corporate. The group is protected from cancer detection in late stages.
  • Healthier beneficiaries' group due to timely detection of silently growing dangerous tumors.
  • PanTum® Detect is not suitable for individuals with a compromised immune system which has a negative effect on circulating macrophage numbers.
  • No screening test provides a result that is 100% accurate or reliable.
  • As per IVD CE validation study:
    • Statistically, 1 in 100 candidates screened with PanTum® Detect will receive a false positive result (they don't have the disease but test positive).
    • Statistically, 2.5 in 100 candidates with the disease, screened with PanTum® Detect will receive false negative result (they do have disease but test negative).
  • False results are a psychological strain for individuals that get screened with PanTum® Detect.

PanTum® Detect: Exclusion Criteria for individuals at the time of sample draw

Individuals who want to undergo PanTum® Detect need to be in a healthy state to ensure highest blood sample quality. To ensure accuracy, the PanTum® Detect blood test requires confirming that each individual's immune system, specifically their macrophages (immune scavenger cells), is not affected by medication, treatment, or illness at the time of sample collection. This ensures reliable detection of elevated levels of bio-markers Apo 10 and TKTL1 in each screened individual's macrophages.

WARNING SIGNS OF CANCER

  • ● Unexplained Weight Loss - An early sign of colon and digestive cancers. It affects your appetite and body's ability to remove waste.
  • ● Shortness of Breath - Lung cancer patients remember noticing this as one of their first symptoms.
  • ● Fatigue or extreme tiredness that doesn't get better with rest. Extreme and prolonged tiredness not alleviated by rest can be a symptom of various illnesses, including some cancers.
  • ● Pelvic or Abdominal Pain - Pain and cramping in the pelvis can be linked with the bloating signs of ovarian cancer.
  • ● Upset Stomach - Stomach cramps or a frequently upset stomach can be a sign of colorectal cancer.
  • ● Rectal Bleeding or blood in stool - Common sign of colorectal cancer. Blood in the toilet should be a big enough sign to see a doctor.
  • ● Feeling full and unable to eat - A sign of ovarian cancer, loss of appetite even when you haven't eaten for a while is tip-off.

CANCER PREVENTION RECOMMENDATIONS

  • ● Eat a diet rich in whole grains, fruits, vegetables, and beans.
  • ● Get vaccinated for HPV and Hepatitis B.
  • ● Avoid Smoking & Tobacco / Betelnut Chewing.
  • ● Avoid or limit alcohol consumption.
  • ● Be physically active.
  • ● Limit consumption of sugar-sweetened drinks.
  • ● Limit consumption of “fast foods” and other processed foods.
  • ● Limit consumption of red and processed meats.
  • ● Maintain a healthy weight.
  • ● Aim for 7-9 hours of consistent sleeping habits per night.
  • ● Limit sedentary time. Take breaks to stand up, stretch, or walk around every hour when engaging in prolonged screen-based activities.

PLEASE NOTE

Cancer can occur in individuals without known risk factors, while exposure to emerging cancer risk factors may not always result in cancer.

The Multi-Cancer Risk Assessment (MCRA) tool helps individuals and health professionals to assess each candidate’s exposure to the risk of developing multiple cancers, i.e., the risk of silent tumor growth going undetected till late stages of metastatic cancer.

The MCRA is a tool to help healthy individuals to personalize their individual exposure to multiple causes & factors leading to silent dangerous tumor growth.

Since symptoms usually don’t show up till late stages of cancer development, early detection through regular multicancer screenings and maintaining a healthy lifestyle are essential preventive actions leading to the reduction of the risk of silent growth of dangerous tumors.

Personal choices individuals make about the way they live can result in a reduced cancer risk exposure, thus improving survival rates for those detected in early stages of localized cancerous tumor growth.

Undergoing screening for multiple cancers simultaneously and adopting a cancer risk reduction lifestyle are the easiest ways to protect everyone from the risk of silent tumor growth undetected.
